parameters:
\n<Ameria>"This place... I've seen it before. This is the Church of
Anatos. No doubt about it."

\n<Roselitte>"To think that such a place was connected here... It's
somewhat imaginable that Priest Abel knew about the
situation."

\n<Lyric>"...I can feel the power of monster taming. It seems like
there are quite a number of monsters outside. For now, this
building seems safe though."
\n<Roselitte>"Do you also know where Deorc is?"

\n<Lyric>"I can tell. Roughly, at least. He's still in Anatos. From
here, it would be in the northern direction, I guess."

\n<Ameria>"From here to the north... Then, the only notable building
would be 'Anatos Castle'."

\n<Ameria>"There should also be a 'prison block' inside the castle.
Maybe Prince Yuri is being held captive there."

\n<Roselitte>"Hmm... In any case, we need to head towards Anatos Castle,
don't we?"

\n<Roselitte>"Lyric, could you go and see if there's a way to infiltrate
the interior of the castle?"

\n<Lyric>"Roger that. But hey, what if I can't get in? Are we going
for a frontal assault?"

\n<Roselitte>"No. Advancing head-on is definitely impossible. Let's hide
here and observe Deorc's movements."

\n<Roselitte>"When Deorc starts his attack again, that's when we'll carry
out the rescue of Prince Yuri or the subjugation of Deorc."

\n<Roselitte>"Ameria, Lyric, this is your last chance to turn back...
Will you come with me?"

\n<Lyric>"...After all this time, you're saying that? I'll go check
quickly, so just wait here."

\n<Ameria>"While you're gone, I'll do some healing. We need to get in
better shape to prepare for the battle."

\n<??>"It's futile to just look around. Deorc is extremely wary of
you all. All the paths into the castle have been sealed
off."

\n<Lyric>"I knew it was you. You suddenly appeared like that before
and it was confusing, but I could never forget that voice!"
\n<Lyric>"I have so many questions for you. Don't move from there!"

\n<Begieade>"Ah, Lyric. How endearing you are. To think you'd accept me
even after death."

\n<Begieade>"Pitiful, miserable, and so very painful... Yet at the same
time, so fleeting and beautiful. Right now, I really want to
embrace you."

\n<Lyric>"Answer me. Why did you resurrect me? What are you planning?
Are you going to use me again to feed on lust?"

\n<Begieade>"So many questions. You know, pushy women tend to be
disliked?"
Begieade laughed heartily and licked his lips.

\n<Begieade>"The taste of lust I fed on from you was indeed marvelous.
The sweetness that springs forth as a beautiful woman is
tormented and resists—it's not something one easily
forgets."

\n<Begieade>"Yes, indeed. I do want to use you. I want to use you, a
succubus, to feed on desires. To satisfy my belly with ripe
and sweet lust."

\n<Begieade>"...But that being said, right now there's no need for your
help, and besides--"
\n<Begieade>"--I didn't resurrect you or anything like that."
\n<Begieade>"...And Lyric, aren't you being a bit selfish?"

\n<Begieade>"'You're using me...' But originally, wasn't it you who
sought me out? Weren't you the one who wished to see your
mother?"

\n<Begieade>"To obtain something, there must be a corresponding price.
He who does not work shall not eat. If you want me to grant
your wish, it's only reasonable that you devote yourself to
me in return."

\n<Lyric>"--Don't dodge the question! You just fed on me without even
trying to bring my mother back to life!"

\n<Lyric>"You kept saying, 'Corrupt that knight! Feed me with lust!'
That's all you ever said! You never tried to fulfill my
wish!"

\n<Lyric>"Why did you target her? Why did it have to be her? Why...
why...!"

\n<Lyric>"Answer me! Why won't you listen to my wish! I've done so
much already! It should be enough! Bring my mother back to
life...! Uwaaaaaaah...!!"
\n<Begieade>"No, no, Lyric. You're making a big mistake."

\n<Begieade>"It's outrageous to say I wouldn't grant your wish. I have
always wanted to grant it, from before and even now."

\n<Begieade>"Don't jump to conclusions. I want you to trust me. It's not
that I didn't grant your wish. I couldn't grant it."
\n<Begieade>"...And the reason I couldn't is because you rejected me."
\n<Begieade>"Calm down. Try to imagine it once more, slowly?"

\n<Begieade>"If at that time you hadn't hesitated, if you had listened
to me and corrupted that knight,"
\n<Begieade>"who do you think you could be with right now...?"
Begieade extended his hand towards Lyric.
\n<Begieade>"Take my hand. And let's become one again."

\n<Begieade>"Take my hand. If you do, surely... I can respond to your
feelings."

\n<Begieade>"Take my hand. If you do, surely, this time for sure... you
will be able to meet your mother."
\n<Begieade>"You will be able to meet your mother."
\n<Begieade>"You will be able to meet your mother."
\n<Begieade>"Come now, come with me. Let's make your wish come true."
\n<Begieade>"...That's fine too. There's no need to rush."

\n<Begieade>"Below here. Did you notice there was another door where you
came through? This is the key to open that door."

\n<Begieade>"Beyond that door lies the underground of Anatos... 'The
Underground Prison District.' If you go through there, you
should be able to sneak into the inner part of the castle,
the prison ward."

\n<Begieade>"The crown prince is being held captive in the prison ward.
Using that, you should be able to meet him without Deorc
finding out."

\n<Begieade>"But be very careful. There are still prisoners who know
nothing of what's happening, and it's hard to say it's a
safe path."

\n<Roselitte>"What exactly are you planning? Aren't you an ally of
Deorc?"
\n<Begieade>"An ally of Deorc? Hmm, whatever do you mean?"

\n<Roselitte>"Don't play dumb. You're the one who gave power to Deorc,
aren't you?"
\n<Begieade>"Yes, yes. Indeed, I am the one who gave power to Deorc."
\n<Begieade>"I am your ally... No, perhaps I should say your lifesaver."

\n<Begieade>"Despite the fact that I'm helping you and many other
humans, you're quite cold, aren't you?"

\n<Begieade>"Pass through the Underground Prison District, sneak into
the inner part of the castle, rescue the crown prince from
the prison ward, and defeat Deorc."

\n<Begieade>"If you do that, this story will come to an end. The country
will be saved, many lives will be spared, and then--"

Roselitte picked up [Key to the Underground Prison
District].
\n<Lyric>"...I'm going to check outside. You all rest here."
\n<Roselitte>"Let's rest a bit until she comes back."

\n<Lyric>"Whew, that was tough. I went to see if we could get into
Anatos Castle but that place is--...what's wrong? Why so
gloomy?"

\n<Ameria>"...Rather, why are you so cheerful? After what just
happened."
\n<Lyric>"...Well, it's not like I'm particularly cheerful but..."
Lyric stared at her own palm.

\n<Lyric>"...Right now, worrying won't give us answers. Let's move
first and think later."
\n<Lyric>"Oh? What's this, are you praising me?"

\n<Roselitte>"It's a far cry from when you were so agitated that you
cried."
\n<Lyric>"Why do you have to throw cold water on it now!?"

\n<Lyric>"Ah, yes, yes... I went to see if we could get into the
castle, but that's a no-go. There doesn't seem to be any
secret passages, and there are too many monsters."

\n<Lyric>"The monsters have gathered inside the castle, spilling out
all the way to the gates. I wish I could show it to you."

\n<Lyric>"Yeah. The monsters are currently surrounding Levee, right?
Maybe this time they're really aiming to take it down."

\n<Lyric>"...In conclusion. Just as Begieade said, there doesn't seem
to be a way into the castle, except maybe underground."
Roselitte stared at the key left behind by Begieade.

\n<Roselitte>"...Begieade is watching over us. No matter where we go,
it's all the same."

\n<Roselitte>"As he said, I'm thinking of heading underground... What do
you all think?"

\n<Ameria>"...Let's proceed underground. In a way, that might be the
safest option."
The three nodded to each other.
